LAGOS – Nigeria’s contingent to the 2019 World Wrestling Championships in Nur-Sultan – the capital city of Kazakhstan – departed the country on Friday, September 13 via Turkish airline flight for the championships. The delegation, which is made up of six athletes – all of whom won gold at the recently concluded 12th African Games (AG) in Morocco – and two coaches, were led by president of the Nigeria Wrestling Federation (NWF), Hon. Daniel Igali. In the Women Wrestling style, World number three, Odunayo Adekuoroye (57kg), winner of a silver medal in the global showpiece in 2017, is joined by African champions, Blessing Onyebuchi (76kg) and Mercy Genesis (50kg) as well as reigning Commonwealth gold medallists Blessing Oborududu (68kg) and Aminat Adeniyi (62kg), while three-time African champion, Emmanuel Ogbonna (74kg), the only male athlete in the team, will be competing in the Freestyle event. In Kazakhstan, the athletes will be under the watchful eyes of coaches; Purity Akuh and Victor Kodei. Medallists at the World Championships, which runs from Saturday, September 14 to 22, will automatically qualify for the 2020 Olympic Games in Tokyo, Japan.